Zuerich 2016}) 5. O-O Ngf6 ({My own practical outing with 4...Nxd7 continued} 
5... g6 $6 6. c3 Ngf6 7. Re1 (7. Qe2 $5 $14) 7... Ne5 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Nxf3+
10. Qxf3 Bg7 11. e5 dxe5 12. dxe5 Nd5 13. Rd1 e6 14. Nc3 O-O 15. Nxd5 exd5 16.
