Re1 Nxe4+ 36. Kg2 Rd7 37. Rd3 {The tension of the hanging pieces finally told
on White.} (37. Nf3 $1 $16 {This is essentially winning if Black doesn't go
into the single-rook ending, and probably that is winning too.} Nxd2 38. Rxe8
Nxf3 39. Kxf3 Rd2 40. Re2 {With White's king being active, this will be a
nightmare to defend, possibly even if all the kingside pawns end up being
